text1: Tom has 14 toy cars. He arranges them in rows of 2. How many rows does he make?
know_more: Divide the total cars by the number in each row.

text1: Sarah has 13 apples. She wants to give one to each of her 13 friends. Does she have enough?
know_more: Compare the number of apples to the number of friends.

text1: There are 25 cookies in a jar. Mom puts 36 more cookies in. How many cookies are there now?
know_more: Add the new cookies to the ones already there.

know_more: Subtract the broken crayons from the total.
